thread.title: Isaiah Jones finds way to end zone for Rockwood
thread.title_full: Isaiah Jones finds way to end zone for Rockwood - PrepXtra Story

author: News Sentinel staff
title: Isaiah Jones finds way to end zone for Rockwood
text:
Running back Isiah Jones wore a path to the end zone for Rockwood High Friday night.
Jones scored three touchdowns — two on rushes and one via a pass — in the host Tigers’ 49-17 victory over Oliver Springs in a Region 2-2A game.
Jones started with a 4-yard scoring run. His other two touchdowns were part of a 28-point scoring outburst in the third quarter. He caught an 18-yard scoring pass from Will Warner and then ran 56 yards for a TD.
Rockwood (5-2, 2-1) rushed for 349 yards. Ryan McCain, Jayden Woods and Joe Ashburn also had scoring runs. Ashburn’s was a 64-yarder.
Joe Tumminello scored on a 23-yard run for Oliver Springs (1-7, 0-4) and Brandon Buck threw a 28-yard touchdown pass to Jeremiah Johnson.
Greeneville 28, Sullivan South 14: Desmond Dabbs scored all the touchdowns for the Greene Devils (6-1, 4-0) in their 1-4A win.
Dabbs first scored on 12-yard run. He then had touchdowns runs of 62, 22 and 41 yards.
Eli Casey threw a touchdown pass to Ahmad Lovell for Sullivan South (4-3, 2-2), and Tyler Cole returned an interception 37 yards.
Pigeon Forge 22, Unicoi County 8: Noah Whaley had a hand in two touchdowns for Pigeon Forge (5-2, 3-1) in a 1-3A game.
Whaley threw a 13-yard touchdown pass to Dawson Day before running 21 yards for a score.
Hunter Hensley had a 23-yard touchdown run for Unicoi County (3-4, 2-2).
Kingston 45, York Institute 15: Paul Bolden and Brett Plemons figured in eight touchdowns for the Yellow Jackets (7-1).
Bolden scored on runs of 41 and 66 yards, part of Kingston’s 448 yards rushing. Plemons had a 2-yard TD run.
Bolden threw a pair of touchdown passes to Plemons, covering 71 and 11 yards.
Plemons then threw a 34-yard scoring pass to Nathan Jones.
Elizabethton 62, Claiborne 14: Hunter Tyree threw three touchdown passes for Elizabethton (6-1, 4-0) in its 1-3A victory.
Tyree connected with three different receivers on his scoring passes. He threw a 10-yarder to Jeremiah Turner, a 21-yarder to Jalen Smith and a 15-yarder to Corey Russell.
Tyree also had a TD reception of sorts, returning an interception 34 yards.
Game Stopped: Gatlinburg-Pittman’s game at Cosby was halted by inclement weather with G-P leading 14-0 in the first quarter. The game will resume at 6 p.m. Monday in Gatlinburg.
